title: China's unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 returns after docking mission
description: BEIJING， Nov. 17 (Xinhua) -- China's unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 landed in north China Thursday evening， after completing the country's first-ever space docking mission.
cleanContent:
The graphics shows the procedure of Shenzhou-8 spacecraft's return to earth on Nov. 17， 2011. (Xinhua/Lu Zhe)

The graphics shows the procedure of Shenzhou-8 spacecraft's return to earth on Nov. 17， 2011. (Xinhua/Lu Zhe)

The re-entry capsule of Shenzhou-8 spacecraft is found at a landing site located in Siziwang Banner in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region， Nov. 17， 2011. The Shenzhou-8 unmanned spacecraft returned to Earth Thursday evening after completing the country's first docking mission with target orbiter Tiangong-1. (Xinhua/Li Gang)

BEIJING, Nov. 17 (Xinhua) -- China's unmanned spacecraft Shenzhou-8 landed in north China Thursday evening, after completing the country's first-ever space docking mission. | |
